    "content": "**B** — This belongs in the Translator's Afterword, specifically in the cross-traditional connections section under existentialist positioning.\n\nThe finding is substantive and genuinely illuminating — the five-point contrast with Heidegger's Dichter sharpens what is distinctive about the author's concept of the Poetic. But it is precisely the kind of interpretive analysis that would be a spoiler in the Preface: the reader needs to arrive at the Appendix passage and feel the force of \"我们正是这样的创造者\" themselves before being told how it differs from Heidegger. In the Afterword, after the reader has encountered both the Poetic (Essay 5) and this closing passage (Appendix), the Dichter contrast becomes a powerful way to articulate what the reader has already experienced. The shift from \"How do I become authentic?\" to \"How do I notice that I already am?\" is itself an experiential payoff that should not be pre-given."
